'''Lee Heider''' (born February 17, 1947) was born in [[Twin Falls, Idaho]].  He is a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]  member of the [[Idaho Senate]], representing the 24th District since 2010. He is also a council member of [[At-Large]].  He received his bachelor's degree from [[Brigham Young University]].  He received his master's of public administration at [[Ball State University]].<ref>http://www.votesmart.org/bio.php?can_id=72381</ref><ref>http://legislature.idaho.gov/senate/membership.cfm</ref>

== Early Life and Career ==
Lee Heider is married to Jan, has six children, and 20 grandchildren.  He is an owner of a flooring company and worked with the [[United States Air Force]].    He received his bachelor's degree from [[Brigham Young University]].  He received his master's of public administration at [[Ball State University]].  Heider is a member of the Twin Falls City Council and Vice Mayor of Twin Falls.<ref>http://www.votesmart.org/bio.php?can_id=72381</ref><ref>http://legislature.idaho.gov/senate/membership.cfm</ref>

== Committees ==
He is a member of:<ref>http://www.leeheider.com/</ref>
* Health and Welfare
* Resources and Environment 
* Joint Finance Appropriations Committee ([[JFAC]])

== Elections ==
Heider defeated incumbent [[Charles Coiner]] in election 2010. Heider received 8,566 votes.<ref>http://www.sos.idaho.gov/elect/results/enr/statewide_total.xml</ref>

== Awards ==
*Eagle Scout and Silver Beaver, [[Boy Scouts of America]]<ref>http://legislature.idaho.gov/senate/membership.cfm</ref>

